# Project foundation

Before substantial work:

1. Read `memory/agreements.md`.
2. Read `memory/now.md` when it exists.
3. Read `memory/intent.md` when product intent or scope matters.
4. Inspect repository and Git state before assumptions or changes.

Follow Git identity and authority rules in `memory/agreements.md`. Use the configured privacy-safe Git identity. Inspect commit metadata before pushing. Do not expose identity values in repository content. Do not commit, push or perform destructive Git operations unless explicitly authorised.

Do not expose personal or local-system information, secrets or private configuration.

## Commit attribution

- Do not add AI authorship or co-author metadata to commit subjects, bodies, trailers, author fields or committer fields.
- Do not use Cursor, cursoragent, ChatGPT, Claude, Copilot, Gemini, Grok, OpenAI or another AI identity as author, committer or co-author.
- Ordinary technical references to AI tools are allowed when they describe the project rather than claim authorship.
- When `scripts/no-ai-attribution.mjs` exists, run `node scripts/no-ai-attribution.mjs install` in a fresh clone before the first commit or push.
- After every commit or amend, run `node scripts/no-ai-attribution.mjs commit HEAD` and inspect the complete commit metadata.
- If a commit operation adds attribution automatically, do not push. Recreate or amend the commit cleanly, verify it again, or stop and report.
- Never treat a failed attribution check as an acceptable warning.

Follow the **Human collaboration and delivery** contract in `memory/agreements.md`. Keep the maintainer in the product-owner and acceptance role rather than making them the default terminal operator. Run technical verification yourself where tools permit. When asked for an implementation prompt, provide one complete copy-pasteable Markdown prompt. Stop before unapproved costly work, new architecture, broad refactoring or test-harness expansion. Establish whether substantial work is an MVP, prototype or complete build before implementation.

When `memory/now.md` points to a `specialist/` file, read that file for the active task. Pointers do not automatically mean every specialist file belongs in default context.

Keep changes focused, verified and proportionate. Do not duplicate full agreements here — they live in `memory/agreements.md`.
